    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-07-03T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-07-03T14:00:00-05:00" n="124"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.85/133: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-03T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >July 3, 1942—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1089. Department’s 753, June 30, 9 p.m.<note n="51" xml:id="d124fn51">Not
                        printed; it inquired whether certain named vessels could be diverted to war
                        shipping.</note> All Chilean vessels under control Government whose approval
                    would have to be obtained before any arrangements could be made. Sub-Secretary
                        Commerce<note n="52" xml:id="d124fn52">Ricardo Heatley.</note> states that
                    to relieve present shortage possibility of allotting additional ships for
                    service between Chile and the United States now under consideration. He promises
                    more specific information about July 9. The ships in question and present trades
                    are as follows: <hi rend="italic">Chollin, Federico Schwager</hi> coastwise
                    coal; <hi rend="italic">Millabu</hi> Peruvian sugar; <hi rend="italic"
                        >Castilla</hi> coastwise; <hi rend="italic">California</hi> single trip
                    Argentine wheat.</p>
                <p>There appears no possibility obtaining Chilean vessels for service other than to
                    the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
